<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="mqlcqe" data-video-descrip="As in the scriptures, The Ark of the Covenant in Raiders of the Lost Ark is an inherently dangerous artifact. Indy and Marion aren't killed by it because Indy remembers the Bible saying not to look upon the open Ark. Those Wacky Nazis aren't so lucky, and pay the price in nightmarish fashion for their greed and arrogance." data-video-title="The Opening of the Ark" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/mqlcqe_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/mqlcqe.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/HolyIsNotSafe" data-video-tropename="Holy Is Not Safe" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="5.00" data-video-rating-count="10" data-video-media-sources="Film/RaidersOfTheLostArk,Main/ArtifactOfDeath" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link featured-widget-vid">
<div class="featured-widget-vid-iframe">
