<h2 class="bold font-l">The Opening of the Ark</h2>
<p class="_pmvv-vidbox-descTxt">
As in the scriptures, The Ark of the Covenant in Raiders of the Lost Ark is an inherently dangerous artifact. Indy and Marion aren't killed by it because Indy remembers the Bible saying not to look upon the open Ark. Those Wacky Nazis aren't so lucky, and pay the price in nightmarish fashion for their greed and arrogance. </p>
</div>
<div class="video-examples-thumbs">
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="zsmv44" data-video-descrip="Meg gets her face melted off by the holiness of the Ark of the Covenant when it's stuffed in her locker." data-video-title="FG Ark of the Covenant" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/zsmv44_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/zsmv44.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/HolyIsNotSafe" data-video-tropename="Holy Is Not Safe" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="WesternAnimation/FamilyGuy" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/zsmv44.jpg">
<p><span class="bold">FG Ark of the C...</span></p>
</a>
</div>
</div>
